      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, a definitive example of Bavarian engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS, delivering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory M-Variable differential lock. This chassis has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including a reinforced rear subframe, rod bearing replacement, and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul using uprated components. The suspension retains original geometry with refreshed bushings, ensuring the sharp turn-in and neutral handling characteristics this platform is known for. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and flawless factory paint depth, this is a turn-key specimen for the serious collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. No accidents. Original paint. Full service records included. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
